        Every puppy goes home vet-checked, vaccinated, dewormed, and microchipped. First-time owners must complete the <a href="https://avs.nparks.gov.sg/pets/licensing-a-pet/applying-for-dog-and-cat-licences/pet-ownership-course/" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">free online pet ownership course</a> before licensing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="first-week" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <CaptionedBlock heading="Your Cockapoo's First Week at Home" imagePosition="none" variant="card">
      <p>Day 0: we deliver free, usually morning or evening, with the playpen, bed, water, and toys set up before your puppy explores. We walk you through all 30+ starter-kit items in person; see <a href="/delivery" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">how our free home delivery and setup works</a>.</p>
      <p>Days 1 to 3: calm and consistent. Same food, fixed times, gentle short play; a sociable cross settles best when the household is present but not overwhelming.</p>
      <p>Days 4 to 7: the routine holds, and it's the window to book the free first lesson; see <a href="/free-training" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">what the free training lesson covers</a>. Start the weekly ear-check habit this week too, while it's still a game.</p>
